ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I definitely recommend the course, best course on MOS.
I would recommend this class for anyone who needs to do cleanroom processing in their research.

Excellent course for EE students or students interested in microelectronics, device/materials research, maybe not so relevant for signals&systems or circuit design tracks, there is a lot of work including HW, lab reports and exams, but it is worth it if this is your field
The course is a very comprehensive and hands-on introduction to semiconductor devices and technology. Great for first year engineering grad students.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course allowed me to deeper understand my research discipline and laid important foundations for my dissertation. I gained practical experience in the cleanroom necessary for future fabrication processes.
This course allowed me to practice my cleanroom techniques in a controlled environment with teaching assitants before having to process in the research cleanroom with more independence.
helped to give me a better understanding in this area and towards future research
The course is relevant to my research and in that respect deepened my understanding of the field and contributed to my dissertation progress.
